-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-12/xfone-rises-mobile-phone-providers-retreat-on-new-licenses.html
(Corrects to remove  Xfone Inc. (XFN)  connection to mobile-phone
license starting in first paragraph.)  Xfone Inc. (XFN)  rose for a second day,
while  Cellcom Israel Ltd. (CEL)  and Partner Communications Co. fell.  Xfone climbed 5.2 percent to 5.063 shekels at 10:24 a.m. in
 Tel Aviv , headed for the biggest increase since Feb. 14.
Cellcom, the countryâ€™s largest mobile-phone company, slumped 3.4
percent to 107.30 shekels on a dividend-adjusted basis. Partner,
the second-largest, dropped 2.5 percent to 64.17 shekels, while
Bezeq Israeli Telecommunication Corp., which offers cell-phone
services through its Pelephone unit, lost 1.4 percent to 10.19
shekels.  The government granted licenses to MIRS Communications
Ltd., a company owned by Patrick Drahi, and Xfone, a company
Xfone Inc. sold to Marathon Telecom Ltd. on Aug. 31.  Hot
Telecommunication System Ltd. (HOT) , a cable and telecommunications
company also owned by Drahi, slipped 0.3 percent to 64.70
shekels.  To contact the reporter on this story:
